metadata.description:
The meeting that started it all: Jeff Hawkins presents his vision of how the principles of the Thousand Brains Theory can be used to build true machine intelligence.

This video covers the inception of the Thousand Brains Project, emphasizing a new 'cortical messaging protocol' (called ‘AI bus’ in this video) and the difference between structured and unstructured AI models. It explores cortical columns, sensorimotor learning, and the architecture of the brain.

00:00 Introduction to the Thousand Brains Project and context for this video by Viviane Clay
01:08 The Meeting Begins!
03:20 Understanding Structured and Unstructured Models
05:34 The Role of Reference Frame
11:46 Brain's Techniques for Spatial Representation
16:52 Building Models and the AI Bus
19:15 Voting Mechanism and Practical Application
24:00 Knowledge Transfer in the Cortex
26:31 Episodic Memory and the Hippocampus
28:18 Language Processing in the Brain
31:27 Engineering the Future of AI
34:40 Defining the Bus Architecture
38:18 Balancing Biological and Artificial Methods
41:39 Conclusion: The Path Forward
